  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6995.9 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (18.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level while providing support on dips toward the 6874 flip point. The PIN regime with 122.7B total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, particularly given the cluster of positive gamma walls from 7000-7100 that will cap upside momentum. Watch for rejection at 7000 and stabilization above 6874, with dealers likely already starting to hedge short delta as we approach the key round number.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong resistance at 7000 with price getting pinned in a tight range between 6900-7000.",
